        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 4:03AM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 403 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hector, or 18 miles northeast of Russellville, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brock Creek Campground...         Beverage Town...
Austin in Conway County...        Jerusalem...
Rupert...                         Scotland...
Claude...                         Hector...
Cleveland...                      Formosa...
Alread...                         Caglesville...
Mountain Man Trailhead...         Appleton...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
